verbs.description: outwhirl (third-person singular simple present outwhirls, present participle outwhirling, simple past and past participle outwhirled)

entries.meaning: (rare, transitive) To surpass in whirling or spinning.
examples: O Cynthia! why so pale? Dost thou lament
Thy wretched neighbour? Grieve to see thy wheel
Of ceaseless change outwhirl'd in human life?
